    "morphology_notes": "Large horizontally-oriented soma at oriens/alveus border. Horizontal dendrites in stratum oriens, densely decorated with long spines. Axon projects vertically through pyramidale and radiatum, ramifies extensively in stratum lacunosum-moleculare with dense terminal arborizations and heavily packed varicosities. Some axon collaterals with boutons in stratum oriens.",
    "electrophysiology_class": "Regular-to-fast spiking with tonic or mildly adapting firing. Pronounced sag response to hyperpolarizing current (Ih via HCN2 h-channels). Theta spiking resonance. High input resistance, slow membrane time constants. Anti-Hebbian LTP dependent on Ca2+-permeable AMPA receptors. Phase-locked to theta rhythms (4-12 Hz)."
